rComments: All lectures were pre-recorded so I guess I can't say much about professor Scott. I really enjoyed the class though. Most of the material was very interesting. There are a lot of readings and the questions associated with them are the questions that show up on exams. Attend discussion group and do the readings.
Unfair marking and prof just gives a bunch of readings
Easy class, shes very nice and caring, i personally found the class kind of boring but being online doesn't help

The prof is terrible to listen to and her content is taught terribly. Assigns about 4-6 readings a week and they're all boring. I was told in my term paper that I should have used some random source to strengthen the paper... wanna tell me how I was supposed to figure that out? DO NOT TAKE
teacherRatingTags: ['Lots of homework', 'Get ready to read', 'Tough grader']

rComments: She is probably a very nice person, but honestly we are paying to be told to read a bunch of sources and be tested on them. The readings are also usually inaccessible to disabled ppl (low quality, crooked scans of a book, can't use a screen reader or search document) :/ pretty disappointing overall
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Graded by few things', 'Test heavy']

rComments: Course load was super heavy and had a lot of readings. Super tough grader and her marking style and rubric is very vague, she was not specific with what she was looking for in assignments and exams and was super difficult to interpret. She was also super unapproachable and unavailable, overall not very helpful, wouldn't recommend her as a prof.

Professor Scott has no intrest in helping you succeed in this class. For example, I did poorly on one paper and tried eveything in my power for a grade reconsideration and she refused to hear me out. She is extremly vague in her lectures and her then picks your work apart. DO NOT TAKE THIS CLASS!
This class is a hit or miss. Everything is based off the online readings so basically you are paying for someone to give you readings you can find yourself for free. Not worth it in my opinion.
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Graded by few things']

rComments: She is okay but is not helpful at all when emailing her (she either won't answer or be disrespectful). She gives very very short lectures, which I could probably find the same information on a Youtube video. She assigns TONS of readings and the midterm, final and project are only based on the readings. Unspecific feedback. Would not recommend.
teacherRatingTags: ['Tough grader', 'Graded by few things', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: The course content was not hard for me, I'm fine with working on my own. Be aware that she will not help you in any situation. If you trust yourself, take it. But the prof will not help you. Her lectures are 10 minutes long and then you are on your own. DGDS are run by TAs and they are useless. Everyone got the same feedback.

I dropped this class before the midterm. I HATED this class. There are no live lectures, but she expects you to read four, 4-6 page articles, each week and talk about it in your DGD. For the midterm, she said to spend 7 hours on EACH MODULE, which was a total of 30 hours! She pushed all her work as a prof onto the TA's, and my TA was rude.
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'So many papers', 'Participation matters']

rComments: Avoid this class at all costs. TAs are rude and class material is subjective to opinion. The professor is also very impatient and disrespectful. Save yourself.

Took this class for an elective during Fall2020 online semester. Every other class I had 90s but this class finishing with a D+ /C-, very hard to get over a 70 on the midterm/papers, the TAs take off 40% if you have grammar mistakes. The lectures online are short but have hours and hours worth of questions for each module.
She does not teach like at all like I do not know what I have learnt at all. I do not get the grading. This by fair my hardest class it makes zero sense to have a prof who does not teach.

She is the best professor i ever have . Any one say she sucks are wrong. I remembered that i had a diffculty with brightspace and video. She email me back very quick and do not feel annoyed by me . Every lectures she gives are understandable. She is so excellent. I did not like women's gender study class and want to switch,but now i love her.

Took this thinking it would be an easy elective and good for GPA.. nope. Im normally a high 80/90s student, and the TA's mark impossibly hard. Even if you're passionate about feminism and women's studies do not take this course. The content is boring and hardly ever even relates to women and you aren't even able to express your own views, not worth

If you want challenge you can have this profs course. She doesn't post power pointso you have to attend the class and take notes in the class. This course doesn't required textbook but there are few readings on the brightspace. She is so strict on marking. I got a really bad result result of the work that I prepared a lot.

Took this class as an elective and I honestly regret it. As a professor she is good. But her TA's mark EXTREMELY tough... I'm a high 70's low 80's student and I barely passed the midterm. Even saw the TA during office hours for a grade reconsideration and nothing was done. I find it weird especially since its a first year class. Wouldn't recommend.

She really knows her stuff and makes her lectures interesting. The assignment and exams are graded toughly so make sure to edit and study. Questions on readings are discussed each class which is the questions used on the exam, but they aren't posted online. I highly recommend this prof, just make sure you go to class or have a friend to send notes.

I am a second year nursing student who took this as an elective and for me it was one of my harder courses. The TA's grade midterm's and exam's extremely tough. I would not recommend this course if your program has a heavy course load, because this will take up most of your time. I do not recommend this course.

I really enjoyed the course because there was a lot of Interesting topics. The prof seems nice but looses patience easily. The workload is extremely heavy, but she gives you the questions that will appear in the exam. Do your readings, and attend class.

Very kind and caring prof. The few times I spoke to her she was super nice. The course material can be controversial but she allows all students to disagree with what she says. Now, this course is NOT an easy A. It was interesting and I learned a lot, but the workload is heavy. Exam questions are given beforehand, but marking is STRICT.
very respectable prof. literally gives you the questions along with a guideline for the answers for the midterm and final. super engaging and great TAs
Love love LOVE. Shes just amazing.

the class I was in had weekly 3 hour lectures and they always flew by. The content was extremely interesting. Ms Scott is clearly passionate about what she's teaching. I learned a lot and would definitely take a class with her again. She told us exactly what would be on the midterm and final which was super helpful. I highly recommend this course.

She is a very cool person, easy to talk to and not super strict. Very kind at heart. Took this course as a mark booster and it wasn't that hard. does not give much feedback on assignment but if you go see her on her office hours you can get feedback that way. during her lectures she does say Um and Uh every .2 seconds which can get annoying

Honestly thought this would be an easy course based on other ppls experiences, however, this was not the case. Super hard marker, no clear feedback so you dont know where you went wrong. Very subjective and heavily opinionated as in, if your opinion doesnt match hers well youre out of luck. If youre looking for an easy A this is not the class

I found the tests were extremely subjective, if you don't have the same opinion as them you won't get a good grade. I asked to get recorrected by someone else and she added 15% to my grade, just to show how subjective this course is. As for teaching, she is a bit boring. The work load is really heavy for a full time student.
teacherRatingTags: ['Graded by few things', 'Tough grader', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: Took this class as an elective and LOVED it! Corrie is super passionate about her subject and it really shows in her lecture. She gives all questions that show up on exams in class which is so helpful. I learned so much!
She's just too booring
Boring

Good professor, very nice and lectures are super chill. Lectures are mostly discussions about the readings. Going to class definitely makes life easier as she basically gives the midterm and exam questions in class, but going to class is not necessary.

AMAZING PROF! Very passionate about feminism! She discusses all the real issues that are going on in the world. Without a doubt best class I've ever taken! I have learned SO MUCH. I definitely recommend her. You have to show up to class and do the readings to understand what's going on, but both are extremely interesting, didn't feel like homework.

She truly has a heart for teaching and if gender studies is your passion she is the teacher for you. Her midterms and exams are exactly the questions she gives you in class, therefore, you don't have to study the whole course load. Lectures are long and filled with people just sharing stories. She is very hard to approach because she's always busy
I really loved this class. I learnt a lot. She's a good professor.

Amazing professor. If you have the chance to take her class I strongly recommend it! Classes are always interesting, but attendance is necessary for a good grade as the questions and discussions in class are all used on the midterm and final exams. All around great teacher and lots of useful information.

By the end I liked the class. She is very passionate about Fem. Often talks fast... which sometimes makes it hard to take notes or understand. Class is important to attend! ALL QUESTIONS ON MIDTERM AND EXAM ARE GIVEN IN CLASS. Very important to do readings before the class, I was lost when I didn't

You have to go to class because she gives the questions of the midterms during the lectures, which can be very long. A tough grader, and you have to red a lot for every class. The material could be better.
I took her class as a first year elective.. Was an easy A If you attend the lectures you will be golden. She gives the exam questions as review questions in each lecture. Easy to understand content

Corrie Scott is an excellent prof, loves it when students discuss and participate in class. The material is not too hard and she goes over the readings, has guest lecturers, etc so it's easy to pay attention. The material itself is fascinating as well, and I would recommend this class to anyone wishing to understand feminism clearly and simply.
Great class.  Extremely hard marker in the mid term and exam.
Great prof. Really kind and wants students to understand. Not the most eloquent lecturer, but it doesn't really matter. One of my favorite profs and favorites classes.

overall, she's a good prof. maybe a bit hard to listen to, like she seems to have too much information to give and doesn't know how to present it, so it all comes out in a disorganized mumble. she takes time to go over each reading, and really wants you to understand. she'll answer all your questions, and is a fair grader.

Great prof, interesting lectures, passionate about subject, will give some exam questions and hints ahead of time. Movie clips used almost every class. Multiple choice, short answers & essay questions plus term project (essay).  Easy A if you attend class/take good notes and do the readings. I highly recommend this class/prof!!

Corrie is definitely my favourite professor I've had so far at my time at Ottawa U. Extremely helpful & available, use of video and guest lectures are great and she also has her TA's lecture which is a nice change of pace. She's also very helpful around exam time and always makes important points clear in lectures. Awesome professor overall.
